        Oxidation system for samples

            A307        
PerkinElmer















Oxidation system for samples

                                                                    - A307                                                            








        Description    


The Model 307 oxidizer makes use of a patented flame oxidation technology, of type "open/close". The result of this is an oxidizer that can expand experimental designs in applications such as liquid scintillation counting. The combustion of sample material increases the accuracy of the LS counting process, because of the lack of color quench, self-absorption, spectral overlap and chemiluminescence. 

This is also a solution for overcoming costly chemical sample preparation, which contributes towards the elimination of the problems associated with non-soluble samples. The item substantially improves precise and effective sample combustion, yielding 100% isotope separation in the case of dual label experiments.



View the catalog

                Go to the PerkinElmer website for more information            


